The paper deals with labeling schemes for dynamic trees, which is a topic in distributed algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the communication complexity of the labeling schemes, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of existing static tree labeling schemes to construct dynamic labeling schemes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper's focus on optimizing label size and communication complexity suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.AL (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
